messages.content:
THOUGHT: The miscompile is due to InstCombine replacing copysign(Mag, Sign) with fabs/fneg purely based on the sign of Sign. This changes NaN sign behavior because copysign preserves the second operand’s sign on NaN, while fabs/fneg force a sign. To fix, I will guard that transform to only apply when the magnitude is known not to be NaN. I’ll wrap the existing known-sign reduction in a check using isKnownNeverNaN(Mag, ...), then submit the patch.

```bash
sed -i '2738,2751c\    if (std::optional<bool> KnownSignBit = computeKnownFPSignBit(
            Sign, /*Depth=*/0, getSimplifyQuery().getWithInstruction(II))) {
      // Only reduce to fabs/fneg if the magnitude cannot be NaN, because
      // copysign preserves the sign of the second operand even for NaN,
      // while fabs/fneg force a specific sign.
      if (isKnownNeverNaN(Mag, getSimplifyQuery().getWithInstruction(II))) {
        if (*KnownSignBit) {
          // If we know that the sign argument is negative, reduce to FNABS:
          // copysign Mag, -Sign --> fneg (fabs Mag)
          Value *Fabs = Builder.CreateUnaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fabs, Mag, II);
          return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, Builder.CreateFNegFMF(Fabs, II));
        }
        // If we know that the sign argument is positive, reduce to FABS:
        // copysign Mag, +Sign --> fabs Mag
        Value *Fabs = Builder.CreateUnaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fabs, Mag, II);
        return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, Fabs);
      }
    }' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCalls.cpp && submit-patch
```

